The paper discusses concentration inequalities for submodular and fractionally subadditive functions of independent random variables, which are topics that are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
